other_tests.findings: Blind-ending fluid filled tubular structure in the right lower quadrant with hyperemia, surrounding edema, and a shadowing appendicolith. The structure is dilated measuring 9-10 mm in the short axis and is non-compressible. The uterus is normal in size with a homogeneous endometrium measuring 4 mm. The ovaries are normal. There is minimal free fluid seen in the pelvis.
